              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-b74c7f85-d824-4b50-9749-73b0458aa1cf');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",
              "  </div>\n",
              "\n",

              "          quickchartButtonEl.disabled = true;  // To prevent multiple clicks.\n",
              "          quickchartButtonEl.classList.add('colab-df-spinner');\n",

              "          }\n",

              "    <script>\n",
              "      const buttonEl =\n",
              "        document.querySelector('#df-d246bdb6-7e28-498a-8a04-2ddf247c6de7 button.colab-df-convert');\n",
              "      buttonEl.style.display =\n",
              "        google.colab.kernel.accessAllowed ? 'block' : 'none';\n",
              "\n",
              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-d246bdb6-7e28-498a-8a04-2ddf247c6de7');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",

              "          const quickchartButtonEl =\n",
              "            document.querySelector('#' + key + ' button');\n",
              "          quickchartButtonEl.disabled = true;  // To prevent multiple clicks.\n",
              "          quickchartButtonEl.classList.add('colab-df-spinner');\n",
              "          try {\n",
              "            const charts = await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction(\n",
              "                'suggestCharts', [key], {});\n",
              "          } catch (error) {\n",
              "            console.error('Error during call to suggestCharts:', error);\n",
              "          }\n",
              "          quickchartButtonEl.classList.remove('colab-df-spinner');\n",
              "          quickchartButtonEl.classList.add('colab-df-quickchart-complete');\n",

        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "\n",
        "num_cols = ['CreditScore','Age','Tenure', 'Balance', 'NumOfProducts', 'EstimatedSalary']\n",

        "for col in num_cols:\n",

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# Step5: Feature Engineering\n",
        "\n",
        "**Create meaningful features :e.g balance per produce, age group, salary bracket and handle missing values**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "odXbqvhFBsde"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# --- Create a copy for feature engineering\n",
        "df_fe = df.copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1ï¸âƒ£ Balance per product\n",
        "# Avoid division by zero\n",
        "df_fe['Balance_per_product'] = df_fe['Balance'] / df_fe['NumOfProducts'].replace(0, np.nan)\n",
        "df_fe['Balance_per_product'].fillna(0, inplace=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2ï¸âƒ£ Salary to balance ratio\n",
        "df_fe['salary_to_balance_ratio'] = df_fe['EstimatedSalary'] / df_fe['Balance'].replace(0, np.nan)\n",
        "df_fe['salary_to_balance_ratio'].replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan, inplace=True)\n",
        "df_fe['salary_to_balance_ratio'].fillna(df_fe['salary_to_balance_ratio'].median(), inplace=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3ï¸âƒ£ Age group buckets\n",
        "age_bins = [0, 25, 35, 45, 55, 65, 100]\n",
        "age_labels = ['<25', '25-34', '35-44', '45-54', '55-64', '65+']\n",
        "df_fe['age_group'] = pd.cut(df_fe['Age'], bins=age_bins, labels=age_labels)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4ï¸âƒ£ Tenure buckets\n",
        "tenure_bins = [-1, 0, 2, 5, 10, 100]\n",
        "tenure_labels = ['0', '1-2', '3-5', '6-10', '10+']\n",
        "df_fe['tenure_bucket'] = pd.cut(df_fe['Tenure'], bins=tenure_bins, labels=tenure_labels)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 5ï¸âƒ£ Flag high balance customers (top 25%)\n",
        "df_fe['high_balance'] = (df_fe['Balance'] > df_fe['Balance'].quantile(0.75)).astype(int)\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Quick check of newly created features\n",
        "df_fe[[\n",
        "    'Balance_per_product',\n",
        "    'salary_to_balance_ratio',\n",
        "    'Age',\n",
        "    'age_group',\n",
        "    'Tenure',\n",
        "    'tenure_bucket',\n",
        "    'high_balance'\n",
        "]].head()\n"

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# **Step6: Preprocessing -encoding and scaling**\n",
        "\n",
        "**we will build a preprocessing**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "RnHuipAwCCtW"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\n",
        "from sklearn.impute import SimpleImputer\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler, OneHotEncoder\n",
        "from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Define target and features\n",
        "target = 'Exited'\n",
        "drop_cols = ['customer_id']\n",
        "\n",
        "# All features except target and drop columns\n",
        "features = [c for c in df_fe.columns if c not in [target] + drop_cols]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Separate numeric and categorical features\n",
        "numeric_features = [\n",
        "    'CreditScore','Age','Tenure','Balance','NumOfProducts','EstimatedSalary',\n",
        "    'Balance_per_product','salary_to_balance_ratio'\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "categorical_features = [\n",
        "    'Geography','Gender','HasCrCard','IsActiveMember',\n",
        "    'age_group','tenure_bucket','high_balance'\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Ensure categorical features are of type object\n",
        "df_fe[categorical_features] = df_fe[categorical_features].astype('object')\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Preprocessing Pipelines\n",
        "\n",
        "# Numeric pipeline: median imputation + standard scaling\n",
        "numeric_transformer = Pipeline([\n",
        "    ('imputer', SimpleImputer(strategy='median')),\n",
        "    ('scaler', StandardScaler())\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Categorical pipeline: most frequent imputation + one-hot encoding\n",
        "categorical_transformer = Pipeline([\n",
        "    ('imputer', SimpleImputer(strategy='most_frequent')),\n",
        "    ('onehot', OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown='ignore', sparse_output=False))\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Combine numeric and categorical pipelines\n",
        "preprocessor = ColumnTransformer([\n",
        "    ('num', numeric_transformer, numeric_features),\n",
        "    ('cat', categorical_transformer, categorical_features)\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Summary\n",
        "print('Numeric features:', numeric_features)\n",
        "print('Categorical features:', categorical_features)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "Xf12cLZu2xs6",
        "outputId": "a5ab581a-79d1-4353-f6d5-d76c6eb442ee"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Numeric features: ['CreditScore', 'Age', 'Tenure', 'Balance', 'NumOfProducts', 'EstimatedSalary', 'Balance_per_product', 'salary_to_balance_ratio']\n",
            "Categorical features: ['Geography', 'Gender', 'HasCrCard', 'IsActiveMember', 'age_group', 'tenure_bucket', 'high_balance']\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# **Step7: Train Test Split**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "NEiL97NPCa4a"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Define features and target\n",
        "X = df_fe[features]\n",
        "y = df_fe[target]\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Split into train and test sets (80/20) with stratification\n",
        "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
        "    X, y,\n",
        "    test_size=0.2,\n",
        "    stratify=y,\n",
        "    random_state=42\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Summary\n",
        "print(f'Train shape: {X_train.shape}, Test shape: {X_test.shape}')\n",
        "print(f'Train Exited proportion: {y_train.mean():.3f}')\n",
        "print(f'Test Exited proportion: {y_test.mean():.3f}')\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "oD_7P7XO228K",
        "outputId": "e445ee62-6f1c-44b2-8a27-a5900a7686ec"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Train shape: (8000, 18), Test shape: (2000, 18)\n",
            "Train Exited proportion: 0.204\n",
            "Test Exited proportion: 0.203\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# **Step8:Train multiple models with a pipeline and compare using cross validation**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "QUnI4LCQCm9Y"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.model_selection import StratifiedKFold, cross_val_score\n",
        "from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\n",
        "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
        "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, GradientBoostingClassifier, AdaBoostClassifier\n",
        "from sklearn.svm import SVC\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Define models\n",
        "models = {\n",
        "    'LogisticRegression': LogisticRegression(max_iter=500, random_state=42),\n",
        "    'RandomForest': RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=200, random_state=42),\n",
        "    'GradientBoosting': GradientBoostingClassifier(n_estimators=200, random_state=42),\n",
        "    'AdaBoost': AdaBoostClassifier(n_estimators=200, random_state=42),\n",
        "    'SVC': SVC(probability=True, random_state=42)\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Stratified K-Fold Cross Validation\n",
        "cv = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=42)\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Evaluate models using ROC-AUC\n",
        "results = {}\n",
        "\n",
        "for name, model in models.items():\n",
        "    # Pipeline: preprocessing + classifier\n",
        "    pipe = Pipeline(steps=[('preprocessor', preprocessor), ('classifier', model)])\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Cross-validation\n",
        "    scores = cross_val_score(pipe, X_train, y_train, cv=cv, scoring='roc_auc', n_jobs=-1)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Store results\n",
        "    results[name] = scores\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Print summary\n",
        "    print(f\"{name} | ROC-AUC: Mean={scores.mean():.4f}, Std={scores.std():.4f}\")\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "7OvpKuJW27ZS",
        "outputId": "046951a4-7ab5-4993-fdfd-6537173afda4"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "LogisticRegression | ROC-AUC: Mean=0.7877, Std=0.0244\n",
            "RandomForest | ROC-AUC: Mean=0.8486, Std=0.0130\n",
            "GradientBoosting | ROC-AUC: Mean=0.8627, Std=0.0097\n",
            "AdaBoost | ROC-AUC: Mean=0.8462, Std=0.0133\n",
            "SVC | ROC-AUC: Mean=0.8351, Std=0.0104\n"
          ]
        }

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.metrics import (\n",
        "    accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score, roc_auc_score,\n",
        "    confusion_matrix, classification_report\n",
        ")\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Select best model and build pipeline\n",
        "best_model = models[best_name]\n",
        "best_pipeline = Pipeline(steps=[('preprocessor', preprocessor), ('classifier', best_model)])\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Fit on full training data\n",
        "best_pipeline.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Predictions\n",
        "y_pred = best_pipeline.predict(X_test)\n",
        "y_proba = best_pipeline.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]  # probability for ROC-AUC\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Metrics\n",
        "acc = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)\n",
        "prec = precision_score(y_test, y_pred)\n",
        "rec = recall_score(y_test, y_pred)\n",
        "f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred)\n",
        "roc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_proba)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Test Accuracy: {acc:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Test Precision: {prec:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Test Recall: {rec:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Test F1-score: {f1:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Test ROC-AUC: {roc:.4f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nClassification Report:\")\n",
        "print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred))\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Confusion Matrix\n",
        "cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(6, 5))\n",
        "sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap=\"Blues\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Predicted')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Actual')\n",
        "plt.title(f'Confusion Matrix ({best_name})')\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()\n"

        "# Step 10. Feature importance (if applicable)"

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "\n",
        "classifier = best_pipeline.named_steps['classifier']\n",
        "\n",
        "if hasattr(classifier, 'feature_importances_'):\n",
        "    # Numeric feature names\n",
        "    numeric_feature_names = numeric_features\n",
        "\n",
        "    # One-hot encoded categorical feature names\n",
        "    onehot_encoder = best_pipeline.named_steps['preprocessor'] \\\n",
        "                    .named_transformers_['cat'] \\\n",
        "                    .named_steps['onehot']\n",
        "    categorical_feature_names_encoded = list(onehot_encoder.get_feature_names_out(categorical_features))\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Combine all feature names\n",
        "    feature_names = numeric_feature_names + categorical_feature_names_encoded\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Get importances\n",
        "    importances = classifier.feature_importances_\n",
        "    fi = pd.Series(importances, index=feature_names).sort_values(ascending=False)[:20]\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Display top 20 features\n",
        "    display(fi)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Plot top 20 feature importances\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\n",
        "    sns.barplot(x=fi.values, y=fi.index, palette='viridis')\n",
        "    plt.title(\"Top 20 Feature Importances\")\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Importance\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"Feature\")\n",
        "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print('Selected model does not provide feature_importances_ attribute.')\n"

            "âœ… Saved pipeline to 'best_churn_pipeline.pkl'\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Sample new customer\n",
        "sample = {\n",
        "    \"RowNumber\": 10001,  # Dummy value to match X_train structure\n",
        "    \"CustomerId\": 373292828,\n",
        "    \"Surname\": \"Doe\",     # Dummy value to match X_train structure\n",
        "    \"CreditScore\": 650,\n",
        "    \"Geography\": \"France\",\n",
        "    \"Gender\": \"Male\",\n",
        "    \"Age\": 40,\n",
        "    \"Tenure\": 3,\n",
        "    \"Balance\": 50000.0,\n",
        "    \"NumOfProducts\": 2,\n",
        "    \"HasCrCard\": 1,\n",
        "    \"IsActiveMember\": 1,\n",
        "    \"EstimatedSalary\": 60000.0\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "sample_df = pd.DataFrame([sample])\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Apply same feature engineering as training data\n",
        "# 1ï¸âƒ£ Balance per product\n",
        "sample_df['Balance_per_product'] = sample_df['Balance'] / sample_df['NumOfProducts'].replace(0, np.nan)\n",
        "sample_df['Balance_per_product'].fillna(0, inplace=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2ï¸âƒ£ Salary to balance ratio\n",
        "sample_df['salary_to_balance_ratio'] = sample_df['EstimatedSalary'] / sample_df['Balance'].replace(0, np.nan)\n",
        "sample_df['salary_to_balance_ratio'].replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan, inplace=True)\n",
        "sample_df['salary_to_balance_ratio'].fillna(df_fe['salary_to_balance_ratio'].median(), inplace=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3ï¸âƒ£ Age group\n",
        "age_bins = [0, 25, 35, 45, 55, 65, 100]\n",
        "age_labels = ['<25', '25-34', '35-44', '45-54', '55-64', '65+']\n",
        "sample_df['age_group'] = pd.cut(sample_df['Age'], bins=age_bins, labels=age_labels)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4ï¸âƒ£ Tenure bucket\n",
        "tenure_bins = [-1, 0, 2, 5, 10, 100]\n",
        "tenure_labels = ['0', '1-2', '3-5', '6-10', '10+']\n",
        "sample_df['tenure_bucket'] = pd.cut(sample_df['Tenure'], bins=tenure_bins, labels=tenure_labels)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 5ï¸âƒ£ High balance flag\n",
        "high_balance_threshold = df_fe['Balance'].quantile(0.75)\n",
        "sample_df['high_balance'] = (sample_df['Balance'] > high_balance_threshold).astype(int)\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Predict using the trained pipeline\n",
        "pred = best_pipeline.predict(sample_df)[0]\n",
        "prob = best_pipeline.predict_proba(sample_df)[0, 1]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Predicted churn: {pred}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Probability of churn: {prob:.3f}\")\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "8cFjvOhz3isG",
        "outputId": "d7c6a390-a8bd-479f-edc2-fd87570f9823"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Predicted churn: 0\n",
            "Probability of churn: 0.030\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
